<button class="w3-button cm-button" onclick="expand('sls')"> // Selective Laser Sintering (SLS) // </button>
<div id="sls" class="w3-container w3-round-large cm-acordian w3-hide">
  Selective Laser Sintering (SLS) is the process of using a laser to selectively sinter or melt layers of material together. This form of additive manufacturing is less common in non-industry use, as the costs of having a high power laser to heat up and melt materials is often over budget for the average person.
  <br>
  While more complicated, this approach does allow for the printing of metal or resins which would otherwise be impossible or far more complex on an FDM machine. In addition to this, the objects produced by SLS printers tend to be much higher in resolution as the laser can very precisely control what is melted and what is not.
